text: Rocky Fork Creek is a stream in Boone County in the U.S. state of Missouri. It is a tributary to Perche Creek.Huntsdale, MO, 7.5 Minute Topographic Quadrangle, USGS, 1967 (1985 rev.) Rocky Fork Creek was named for the limestone deposits near a fork in the watercourse. The Rocky Fork Lakes Conservation Area is named after the stream. ==See also== *List of rivers of Missouri ==References== Category:Rivers of Boone County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Missouri
